headline.main: NEW-YORK HISTORICAL SOCIETY.; Semi-Centennial Anniversary. DINNER AT THE ASTOR HOUSE. SPEECH OF HON. ROBERT C. WINTHROP. Addresses of Dr. John W. Francis, Mr. Bancroft, Mr. Bryant, Mr. Bradish and others. THE HISTORICAL SOCIETY.

docs.lead_paragraph: The First Semi Centennial Anniversary of the New-York Historical Society was celebrated yesterday, with appropriate and highly interesting ceremonies. Fifty years have elapsed since this Society was established, and of its original founders but very few remain. Among the number present on this occasion were Dr. JOHN W. FRANCIS, Rev. Dr. MATHEWS and Hon. CHARLES KING.--first members.

headline.main: LATER FROM CUBA.; ARRIVAL OF THE OAHAWBA. Further Intelligence from Havana--The Threatened Outbreak--Slaves Landed--Municipal Affairs, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Mail steamship Cahawba, R. W. SHUFELDT commander, from Now-Or. leans the 9th and Havana the 12th, arrived here on Saturday afternoon. After leaving Havana, she experienced very severe weather, and was compelled to put into Norfolk to replenish her coal, which detained her thirty six hours.

headline.main: ROMAN CATHOLIC EXCITMENT.; Collision between a Bishop and Priest in Hartford. Death of Father Brady--Refusal of the Church Rites by the Bishop.

docs.lead_paragraph: Right Reverend JOHN BRADY, who has been about 18 years the respected pastor of the Roman Catholic Church of this city, died at his residence in Talcott-street, at about 8 o'clock last evening, (Nov 16.) after an illness of 24 hours from an attack of the cholera. headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; NEW-YORK County Canvassers. The Wreck of the New Era. City Mortality. A Suspicious Pedestrian.

docs.lead_paragraph: FIFTH DAY'S SESSION. The New-York Board of County Canvassers assembled at noon on Saturday, at the Chamber of Aldermen, City Hall. At 10 minutes past 12 o'clock, the Board was organized, and on the calling of the roll, the following Supervisors answered to their names : Messrs. BROWN, BLUNT, BAIRD, HOFFMIRE, VOORHIS, WAKEMAN, COVERT, KELLY, ELY AND DRAKE.

headline.main: FURTHER FROM MEXICO.; Battle of Campe de Gurrere--Mexican Blockading Vessel Wrecked--Seventy Lives Lost. Reported Victory of Alvarez over the Government Forces

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Orizaba, Capt. FORBES, arrived here this morning, promptly, as due. She left Vera Cruz on the 8th inst. She brings $18,333 in specie. Captain FORDES reports that the American bark Avalanche, Capt. STEWART, foundered at sea, October. Her captain and crew saved themselves in their boats.
